## Running the Brain

```bash
# From this directory:
neurogrim score --registry .claude/brain-registry.json
neurogrim health --registry .claude/brain-registry.json
neurogrim narrate --hat visionary --registry .claude/brain-registry.json
neurogrim validate --registry .claude/brain-registry.json

# Run the bundled sensory tools (CMDBs auto-update):
neurogrim sensory test-health --project-root . > .claude/test-health-cmdb.json
neurogrim sensory code-quality --project-root . > .claude/code-quality-cmdb.json
neurogrim sensory deploy-readiness --project-root . > .claude/deploy-readiness-cmdb.json
```

## Cultural substrate

`.claude/culture.yaml` is byte-identical to the canonical LSP Brains
federation copy. Five values as invariants — `positivity`, `integrity`,
`honesty`, `critical_but_kind`, `respect`. They can only tighten, never
loosen.

## The PostToolUse hook

`.claude/settings.local.json` (gitignored) wires a PostToolUse hook that
records every Skill invocation to `.claude/brain/invocation-ledger.jsonl`.
Substrate for the `operator-calibration` primitive (spec §17.12).

## What agents working here should know

1. **The three weighted domains gate scoring.** Effective scores roll up
   into the unified score; per-domain trends drive trajectory analysis.
2. **Advisory domains are observability-only at v1.** They surface
   signal without gating. Promotion to weighted requires the spec §15.5
   discipline (calibration audit + ledger entry).
3. **The cultural substrate applies after hats and human-comms.**
4. **Author project-specific skills via `neurogrim skill new <name>`.**

